    "profile": "[b]Alyssa Michelle Stephens[/b], better known as [a10439215], formerly [b]Mulatto[/b] or [b]Miss Mulatto[/b], was born on December 22, 1998 in Toledo, Ohio. An American rapper, reality TV star and former drag racer of Ethiopian descent, Miss Mulatto is the younger cousin of rapper [a=Ray Cash]. \r\nShe uses [b]Latto[/b] as her stage name since January 2021 after receiving racial criticism for her former stage name [a7272502].\r\n\r\nIn 2016, after quitting drag racing and dropping out of high school, she found fame and popularity after appearing on the first season of [a=Jermaine Dupri]'s reality contest show, [i]The Rap Game[/i], which she won. Shortly after winning the first contest, Mulatto released her debut single, \"No More Talkin'\".\r\n\r\nThis success later was baffled throughout 2016 by feuds she was involved in including [a=Toni Romiti] and [a=Keke Palmer]. Mulatto stirred up more violent controversy after getting into fights with Supa Peach and [a=Foxy Brown].\r\n\r\nIn 2017, after a fallo",
